orwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]},{"name":"Llywelyn","meanings":["(Welsh)  See  Llewelyn ."]},{"name":"Llewellyn","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Llewelyn ap Gwrgan of Cydweli was born in 1075, his father, Gwrgan ap Ifor, was 45 and his mother, Mrs. Gwrgan ap Ifor, was 27. He had at least 3 sons with Joan."},"et":{"1075–":"1075–Surnud","1075–Male":"1075–Surnud","1078–Female":"1078–Surnud","1104–Male":"1104–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1030–Male":"1030–Surnud","1049–Female":"1049–Surnud","1049":"1049","1104":"1104","1078":"1078","1075":"1075","Abt 1104":"umbes 1104","1030":"1030","about 1075":"umbes 1075","Wales":"Wales"},"fi":{"1075–":"1075–Kuollut","1075–Male":"1075–Kuollut","1078–Female":"1078–Kuollut","1104–Male":"1104–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1030–Male":"1030–Kuollut","1049–Female":"1049–Kuollut","1049":"1049","1104":"1104","1078":"1078","1075":"1075","Abt 1104":"noin 1104","1030":"1030","about 1075":"noin 1075","Wales":"Wales"},"fr":{"1075–":"1075–Décédé","1075–Male":"1075–Décédé","1078–Female":"1078–Décédée","1104–Male":"1104–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","1030–Male":"1030–Décédé","1049–Female":"1049–Décédée","1049":"1049","1104":"1104","1078